## {{ rule.title }}

[26 U.S.C. § 1211(b)](https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=granuleid:USC-prelim-title26-section1211&num=0&edition=prelim) caps an individual's annual deductible net capital loss at **{{ rule.inputs_by_key["us.constants.capital_loss_limit"].value | money(currency="USD") }}** (`$3,000` normally, `$1,500` for married filing separately). Any net loss above that cap doesn't disappear — [§ 1212](https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=granuleid:USC-prelim-title26-section1212&num=0&edition=prelim) carries it forward to next year, where it preserves its short-term or long-term character. Net capital gain, in contrast, is taxed in full at this stage and the preferential-rate logic at US25-09 sorts the long-term portion onto the qualified-dividends/cap-gain worksheet.

{% set capital = rule.outputs[0].value | from_json -%}
Combining the [Schedule D](https://www.irs.gov/forms-pubs/about-schedule-d-form-1040) buckets from US25-03 with the [§ 1256](https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=granuleid:USC-prelim-title26-section1256&num=0&edition=prelim) split from US25-04, the net capital position **after [§ 1256](https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=granuleid:USC-prelim-title26-section1256&num=0&edition=prelim) mark-to-market** is **{{ capital.net_capital_after_1256_usd | money(currency="USD") }}**.

Applying [§ 1211](https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=granuleid:USC-prelim-title26-section1211&num=0&edition=prelim) / § 1212:

- [Form 1040](https://www.irs.gov/forms-pubs/about-form-1040) line 7a (the amount that flows into AGI): **{{ capital.form_1040_line_7a_usd | money(currency="USD") }}**
- Capital loss deduction taken in 2025 (capped at the [§ 1211(b)](https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=granuleid:USC-prelim-title26-section1211&num=0&edition=prelim) limit): **{{ capital.capital_loss_deduction_2025_usd | money(currency="USD") }}**
- Tentative capital-loss carryforward to 2026 under § 1212: **{{ capital.tentative_capital_loss_carryforward_2026_usd | money(currency="USD") }}**

Line 7a feeds AGI (US25-07); the carryforward is preserved for next year's return; the long-term gain piece (if any) drives the preferential-rate worksheet at US25-09.

